				<pubDate>Sat, 13 Jun 2020 14:12:06 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DrAkimoto</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5255688</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">nitpicks</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">boop</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>to keep guard over SCP-5062.</p> </blockquote> <p>Probably a better way to say this but it's not a big deal.</p> <blockquote> <p>The room contains a king-sized bed, a writing desk, a mini-fridge and a nightstand containing a copy of the King James Bible.</p> </blockquote> <p>Comma after mini-fridge</p> <blockquote> <p>The size and specific form of these scissors will vary depending on the trapped individual, but are consistently at least 7.5cm long.</p> </blockquote> <p>Don't think you need this comma.</p> <blockquote> <p>Following exit, the victim may experience additional symptoms including:</p> </blockquote> <p>Something about &quot;following exit&quot; feels wonky</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>Not much else to say, this is short, concise, and super punchy; a perfect example of a short-form article that works. An easy +1 from me.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
